1
00:00:00.070 --> 00:00:05.580
With Verizon Messages, keeping your conversations going has never been easier.

2
00:00:05.580 --> 00:00:09.530
Let's go over some basic Verizon Messaging features to get you started.

3
00:00:09.530 --> 00:00:15.379
Begin by tapping the Verizon Messages icon from any Home screen to open the app.

4
00:00:15.379 --> 00:00:21.550
To send a text message, tap the Compose icon in the upper right hand corner of the screen.

5
00:00:21.550 --> 00:00:25.570
Start typing the name or number of the person you want to send the message to and you'll

6
00:00:25.570 --> 00:00:32.210
see matching contacts. Tap the one you want.
Addressing a message to more than one person

7
00:00:32.210 --> 00:00:38.000
will start a group conversation.
To write your message, tap in the message

8
00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:45.000
area and start typing.
When your message is complete, tap Send.

9
00:00:47.039 --> 00:00:52.200
Responses to your text will be seen just below the message you sent.

10
00:00:52.289 --> 00:00:59.239
To leave this conversation and see the list of all your conversations, tap the Back button.

11
00:00:59.239 --> 00:01:04.500
When you get a new message from someone, their conversation jumps to the top of the list.

12
00:01:04.500 --> 00:01:09.909
Tap the conversation to see the new message.
Then reply by tapping the text box and entering

13
00:01:09.909 --> 00:01:16.900
your message. When done, tap Send.

14
00:01:16.900 --> 00:01:21.500
When words just aren't enough, express yourself in pictures.

15
00:01:21.500 --> 00:01:25.500
To add a picture to a message, simply tap the Plus button.

16
00:01:26.000 --> 00:01:31.000
Then tap Picture. You can attach pictures that are already on your phone,

17
00:01:31.100 --> 00:01:37.700
or take a new one to share.
Choose your photo and tap Attach.

18
00:01:37.800 --> 00:01:44.000
Tap the text box to add a message to
go with your picture.

19
00:01:44.200 --> 00:01:50.000
When your message is complete, tap Send.

20
00:01:51.000 --> 00:01:56.400
For added creativity, Verizon Messages lets you create a postcard or add personal touches

21
00:01:56.400 --> 00:02:01.899
to pictures using any combination of the collage, caption and sketch features.

22
00:02:01.899 --> 00:02:07.000
You can create a collage with up to five pictures, add captions and choose your fonts, pinch

23
00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:14.000
to resize and reposition, or use your fingers to sketch right on the image.

24
00:02:14.300 --> 00:02:20.000
For more options, tap the Menu icon in the upper left.

25
00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:25.900
You can scroll down to get Tips and Reminders and see What's New, like Integrated Messaging.

26
00:02:25.900 --> 00:02:31.150
Integrated Messaging lets you send and receive messages on your tablet and computer, in addition

27
00:02:31.150 --> 00:02:35.910
to your phone.
To see other useful features, tap Settings.

28
00:02:35.910 --> 00:02:41.660
From here, you can personalize your conversations with different colors and font sizes, or set

29
00:02:41.660 --> 00:02:45.820
up an Auto Reply to let people know you're busy when they text you.

30
00:02:45.820 --> 00:02:51.090
These are just a few of the ways Verizon Messages makes texting easy and fun.

31
00:02:51.090 --> 00:02:57.310
To learn more about Verizon Messages, please visit verizonwireless.com/verizonmessages